posts.description:
Wild Dunedin üåøüåæ
This place really is full of surprises, from the dramatic coastline, the history and culture, the people and the wildlife. I already loved New Zealand, but this trip has made me love it so much more.
.
I was lucky enough to hang out with over 15 other passionate photographers, conservationists and environmentalists over the weekend. I've tagged them all on this photo, so make sure you tap on the photo to check out all of these inspirational human beings.
.
@dunedinnz #WildDunedin #WildDunedinInstameet

Morning üíû‚úß
There are some sunrises that will stay with you forever. This is one of them. Watching the sunrise over the Otago Peninsula in Dunedin from the balcony of my room at @larnachcastle with some of the most inspirational crew i've had the pleasure of hanging out with. A collective of likeminded passionate conservationists and environmentalists, who are also photographers all coming together to learn more about how we can help protect and conserve the future of some of the most vulnerable species on the planet. Dunedin has some of the most beautiful wildlife in the world, and also some of the most threatened. Spending the weekend seeing all these beautiful animals in the wild has made my heart sing. It's a beautiful world out there.
.
@dunedinnz #WildDunedin #WildDunedinInstameet

Coming home üåøüåæ
Can you see those three little black and white dots on the beach? That's Todd escorting his girlfriend and her friend back up the beach away from the prying eyes of two rather large sea lions (also endangered) that are on the beach. These three are rare Yellow Eyed Penguins coming home for the night. Some of the rarest penguins you'll ever be lucky enough to see should you visit the @penguin.place in Dunedin. Todd was so happy when he saw his girlfriend, he kept skipping around and running circles around her. Even Penguins are romantic!
.
@dunedinnz #WildDunedin #WildDunedinInstameet #naturefrother

Penguin Place üêßüêßüêß
How cute is this little guy!! He's an Erect Crested Penguin, known only to New Zealand, he's currently in the rehabilitation center at Penguin Place.

Penguin Place, located only a 30minute drive from Dunedin city is a private conservation reserve dedicated to helping the wild population of endangered Yellow Eyed Penguin survive. They do amazing work and is well worth the visit, places like this are why species are coming back from near extinction. 
Unique to New Zealand the yellow-eyed penguin is thought to be one of the world's rarest penguin species, with less than 4000 left in the wild. 
We were lucky enough to see some Yellow Eyed Penguins in the wild at @penguin.place waddling up the beach after being out all day swimming and catching food. 
We got to watch the penguins, from within a couple of meters, from inside bunkers in the dunes just behind the beach, sea lions on the beach and stand within 3 meters of fur seals on one of the most stunning stretches of coastline i've ever seen. Definitely one of my favourite experiences.
.
@dunedinnz #WildDunedin #WildDunedinFestival

Wild Dunedin üåæüåø
If you've been following my Instastories over the last few days you'd know that i'm currently in @dunedinnz exploring the wild side of Dunedin, from the numerous rare and endangered animals, to their sanctuaries and the stunning coastline and mountains around Dunedin. This place is so much more than i had ever expected, the wildlife, the natural beauty, and the fact that it's only a short 3.5hr flight from home is amazing. I've been chilling out with Penguins, Sea Lions, Albatross, Kiwi, Kaka and more. In love with Dunedin ‚ù§Ô∏è
